verses.text_plain: Give ear, O my people, to my law: incline your ears to the words of my mouth.
verses.verse_html:
1Give ear, O my people, to my law: incline your ears to the words of my mouth. ▼
▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Asaph to give instruction

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Asaph to give instruction
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Asaph to give instruction

verses.text_plain: I will open my mouth in a parable: I will utter dark sayings of old:
verses.verse_html: 2I will open my mouth in a parable: I will utter dark sayings of old:

verses.text_plain: Which we have heard and known, and our fathers have told us.
verses.verse_html: 3Which we have heard and known, and our fathers have told us.

verses.text_plain: We will not hide them from their children, shewing to the generation to come the praises of the Lord, and his strength, and his wonderful works that he hath done.
verses.verse_html: 4We will not hide them from their children, shewing to the generation to come the praises of the Lord, and his strength, and his wonderful works that he hath done.

verses.text_plain: For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:
verses.verse_html: 5For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:

tokens.text: that they should make them known

verses.text_plain: That the generation to come might know them, even the children which should be born; who should arise and declare them to their children:
verses.verse_html: 6That the generation to come might know them, even the children which should be born; who should arise and declare them to their children:

verses.text_plain: That they might set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his commandments:
verses.verse_html: 7That they might set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his commandments:

verses.text_plain: And might not be as their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation; a generation that set not their heart aright, and whose spirit was not stedfast with God.
verses.verse_html:
8And might not be as their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation; a generation that set not their heart aright, and whose spirit was not stedfast with God. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. that prepared not their heart

tokens.text: And might not be as their fathers

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that…: Heb. that prepared not their heart
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. that prepared not their heart

verses.text_plain: The children of Ephraim, being armed, and carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle.
verses.verse_html:
9The children of Ephraim, being armed, and carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle. ▼
▼ carrying: Heb. throwing forth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ carrying: Heb. throwing forth

verses.text_plain: They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law;
verses.verse_html: 10They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law;

verses.text_plain: And forgat his works, and his wonders that he had shewed them.
verses.verse_html: 11And forgat his works, and his wonders that he had shewed them.

verses.text_plain: Marvellous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.
verses.verse_html: 12Marvellous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.

verses.text_plain: He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; and he made the waters to stand as an heap.
verses.verse_html: 13He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; and he made the waters to stand as an heap.

tokens.text: and caused them to pass through

verses.text_plain: In the daytime also he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a light of fire.
verses.verse_html: 14In the daytime also he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a light of fire.

verses.text_plain: He clave the rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink as out of the great depths.
verses.verse_html: 15He clave the rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink as out of the great depths.

verses.text_plain: He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.
verses.verse_html: 16He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.

verses.text_plain: And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the most High in the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 17And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the most High in the wilderness.

verses.text_plain: And they tempted God in their heart by asking meat for their lust.
verses.verse_html: 18And they tempted God in their heart by asking meat for their lust.

verses.text_plain: Yea, they spake against God; they said, Can God furnish a table in the wilderness?
verses.verse_html:
19Yea, they spake against God; they said, Can God furnish a table in the wilderness? ▼
▼ furnish: Heb. order

footnotes.body_html: ▼ furnish: Heb. order

verses.text_plain: Behold, he smote the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed; can he give bread also? can he provide flesh for his people?
verses.verse_html: 20Behold, he smote the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed; can he give bread also? can he provide flesh for his people?

verses.text_plain: Therefore the Lord heard this, and was wroth: so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel;
verses.verse_html: 21Therefore the Lord heard this, and was wroth: so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel;

verses.text_plain: Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation:
verses.verse_html: 22Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation:

verses.text_plain: Though he had commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,
verses.verse_html: 23Though he had commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,

verses.text_plain: And had rained down manna upon them to eat, and had given them of the corn of heaven.
verses.verse_html: 24And had rained down manna upon them to eat, and had given them of the corn of heaven.

verses.text_plain: Man did eat angels’ food: he sent them meat to the full.
verses.verse_html:
25Man did eat angels’ food: he sent them meat to the full. ▼
▼ Man…: or, Every one did eat the bread of the mighty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Man…: or, Every one did eat the bread of the mighty
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Man…: or, Every one did eat the bread of the mighty

verses.text_plain: He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven: and by his power he brought in the south wind.
verses.verse_html:
26He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven: and by his power he brought in the south wind. ▼
▼ to blow: Heb. to go

footnotes.body_html: ▼ to blow: Heb. to go

verses.text_plain: He rained flesh also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea:
verses.verse_html:
27He rained flesh also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea: ▼
▼ feathered…: Heb. fowl of wing

footnotes.body_html: ▼ feathered…: Heb. fowl of wing

verses.text_plain: And he let it fall in the midst of their camp, round about their habitations.
verses.verse_html: 28And he let it fall in the midst of their camp, round about their habitations.

verses.text_plain: So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own desire;
verses.verse_html: 29So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own desire;

verses.text_plain: They were not estranged from their lust. But while their meat was yet in their mouths,
verses.verse_html: 30They were not estranged from their lust. But while their meat was yet in their mouths,

verses.text_plain: The wrath of God came upon them, and slew the fattest of them, and smote down the chosen men of Israel.
verses.verse_html:
31The wrath of God came upon them, and slew the fattest of them, and smote down the chosen men of Israel. ▼
▼ smote…: Heb. made to bow
 , ▼
▼ chosen…: or, young men

footnotes.body_html: ▼ smote…: Heb. made to bow
▼ chosen…: or, young men

verses.text_plain: For all this they sinned still, and believed not for his wondrous works.
verses.verse_html: 32For all this they sinned still, and believed not for his wondrous works.

verses.text_plain: Therefore their days did he consume in vanity, and their years in trouble.
verses.verse_html: 33Therefore their days did he consume in vanity, and their years in trouble.

verses.text_plain: When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned and enquired early after God.
verses.verse_html: 34When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned and enquired early after God.

verses.text_plain: And they remembered that God was their rock, and the high God their redeemer.
verses.verse_html: 35And they remembered that God was their rock, and the high God their redeemer.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless they did flatter him with their mouth, and they lied unto him with their tongues.
verses.verse_html: 36Nevertheless they did flatter him with their mouth, and they lied unto him with their tongues.

verses.text_plain: For their heart was not right with him, neither were they stedfast in his covenant.
verses.verse_html: 37For their heart was not right with him, neither were they stedfast in his covenant.

tokens.text: with him, neither were they stedfast

verses.text_plain: But he, being full of compassion, forgave their iniquity, and destroyed them not: yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not stir up all his wrath.
verses.verse_html: 38But he, being full of compassion, forgave their iniquity, and destroyed them not: yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not stir up all his wrath.

verses.text_plain: For he remembered that they were but flesh; a wind that passeth away, and cometh not again.
verses.verse_html: 39For he remembered that they were but flesh; a wind that passeth away, and cometh not again.

verses.text_plain: How oft did they provoke him in the wilderness, and grieve him in the desert!
verses.verse_html:
40How oft did they provoke him in the wilderness, and grieve him in the desert! ▼
▼ provoke: or, rebel against

footnotes.body_html: ▼ provoke: or, rebel against

verses.text_plain: Yea, they turned back and tempted God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 41Yea, they turned back and tempted God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.

verses.text_plain: They remembered not his hand, nor the day when he delivered them from the enemy.
verses.verse_html:
42They remembered not his hand, nor the day when he delivered them from the enemy. ▼
▼ from…: or, from affliction

footnotes.body_html: ▼ from…: or, from affliction

verses.text_plain: How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Zoan:
verses.verse_html:
43How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Zoan: ▼
▼ wrought: Heb. set

footnotes.body_html: ▼ wrought: Heb. set

verses.text_plain: And had turned their rivers into blood; and their floods, that they could not drink.
verses.verse_html: 44And had turned their rivers into blood; and their floods, that they could not drink.

verses.text_plain: He sent divers sorts of flies among them, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.
verses.verse_html: 45He sent divers sorts of flies among them, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.

verses.text_plain: He gave also their increase unto the caterpiller, and their labour unto the locust.
verses.verse_html: 46He gave also their increase unto the caterpiller, and their labour unto the locust.

verses.text_plain: He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycomore trees with frost.
verses.verse_html:
47He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycomore trees with frost. ▼
▼ destroyed: Heb. killed
 , ▼
▼ frost: or, great hailstones

footnotes.body_html: ▼ destroyed: Heb. killed
▼ frost: or, great hailstones

verses.text_plain: He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.
verses.verse_html:
48He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts. ▼
▼ gave…: Heb. shut up
 , ▼
▼ hot…: or, lightnings

footnotes.body_html: ▼ gave…: Heb. shut up
▼ hot…: or, lightnings

verses.text_plain: He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and trouble, by sending evil angels among them.
verses.verse_html: 49He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and trouble, by sending evil angels among them.

verses.text_plain: He made a way to his anger; he spared not their soul from death, but gave their life over to the pestilence;
verses.verse_html:
50He made a way to his anger; he spared not their soul from death, but gave their life over to the pestilence; ▼
▼ He made…: Heb. He weighed a path
 , ▼
▼ life…: or, beasts to the murrain

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He made…: Heb. He weighed a path
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He made…: Heb. He weighed a path

footnotes.body_text: ▼ life…: or, beasts to the murrain
footnotes.body_html: ▼ life…: or, beasts to the murrain

verses.text_plain: And smote all the firstborn in Egypt; the chief of their strength in the tabernacles of Ham:
verses.verse_html: 51And smote all the firstborn in Egypt; the chief of their strength in the tabernacles of Ham:

verses.text_plain: But made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.
verses.verse_html: 52But made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.

verses.text_plain: And he led them on safely, so that they feared not: but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.
verses.verse_html:
53And he led them on safely, so that they feared not: but the sea overwhelmed their enemies. ▼
▼ overwhelmed: Heb. covered

footnotes.body_html: ▼ overwhelmed: Heb. covered

verses.text_plain: And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain, which his right hand had purchased.
verses.verse_html: 54And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain, which his right hand had purchased.

verses.text_plain: He cast out the heathen also before them, and divided them an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.
verses.verse_html: 55He cast out the heathen also before them, and divided them an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.

verses.text_plain: Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies:
verses.verse_html: 56Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies:

verses.text_plain: But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers: they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.
verses.verse_html: 57But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers: they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.

verses.text_plain: For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.
verses.verse_html: 58For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.

tokens.text: For they provoked him to anger

verses.text_plain: When God heard this, he was wroth, and greatly abhorred Israel:
verses.verse_html: 59When God heard this, he was wroth, and greatly abhorred Israel:

verses.text_plain: So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent which he placed among men;
verses.verse_html: 60So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent which he placed among men;

verses.text_plain: And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy’s hand.
verses.verse_html: 61And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy’s hand.

verses.text_plain: He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was wroth with his inheritance.
verses.verse_html: 62He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was wroth with his inheritance.

verses.text_plain: The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage.
verses.verse_html:
63The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage. ▼
▼ given…: Heb. praised

footnotes.body_html: ▼ given…: Heb. praised

verses.text_plain: Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.
verses.verse_html: 64Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.

verses.text_plain: Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.
verses.verse_html: 65Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.

verses.text_plain: And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he put them to a perpetual reproach.
verses.verse_html: 66And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he put them to a perpetual reproach.

verses.text_plain: Moreover he refused the tabernacle of Joseph, and chose not the tribe of Ephraim:
verses.verse_html: 67Moreover he refused the tabernacle of Joseph, and chose not the tribe of Ephraim:

verses.text_plain: But chose the tribe of Judah, the mount Zion which he loved.
verses.verse_html: 68But chose the tribe of Judah, the mount Zion which he loved.

verses.text_plain: And he built his sanctuary like high palaces, like the earth which he hath established for ever.
verses.verse_html:
69And he built his sanctuary like high palaces, like the earth which he hath established for ever. ▼
▼ established: Heb. founded

footnotes.body_html: ▼ established: Heb. founded

verses.text_plain: He chose David also his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds:
verses.verse_html: 70He chose David also his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds:

verses.text_plain: From following the ewes great with young he brought him to feed Jacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.
verses.verse_html:
71From following the ewes great with young he brought him to feed Jacob his people, and Israel his inheritance. ▼
▼ following: Heb. after

footnotes.body_html: ▼ following: Heb. after

verses.text_plain: So he fed them according to the integrity of his heart; and guided them by the skilfulness of his hands.
verses.verse_html: 72So he fed them according to the integrity of his heart; and guided them by the skilfulness of his hands.
